---
export const prerender = true;
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Terms of Service">
  <div class="max-w-3xl">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Terms of Service</h1>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-8">Last updated March 2026</p>

    <div class="space-y-6 text-gray-600">
      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">1. Acceptance of Terms</h2>
        <p>
          By accessing or using Runners In Need ("the platform"), you agree to be bound
          by these Terms of Service. If you do not agree, do not use the platform.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">2. Description of Service</h2>
        <p>
          Runners In Need is a free community bulletin board that connects people who
          want to donate running gear with organizations that need it. The platform is a
          personal project operated by Nick Coury. It is provided "as is" at no cost to
          anyone.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          The platform is passive &mdash; organizations post needs, donors browse and
          pledge. No money changes hands on this platform. There are no fees, no
          payment processing, and no donations to the platform itself.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">3. User Responsibilities</h2>
        <p>By using the platform, you agree to:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>Provide accurate and truthful information in your listings and profile</li>
          <li>Use the platform only for lawful purposes</li>
          <li>Not post fraudulent, misleading, or deceptive content</li>
          <li>Not use the platform to harass, spam, or abuse other users</li>
          <li>Not attempt to buy or sell goods through the platform &mdash; all gear must be donated freely</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">4. Donor Responsibilities</h2>
        <p>If you pledge gear through the platform, you certify that:</p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>Items are in safe, wearable condition</li>
          <li>Items have not been recalled by the manufacturer</li>
          <li>Items have been cleaned before donation</li>
          <li>You have the right to give the items away</li>
          <li>You are not donating items that pose a known safety hazard</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2">
          The platform does not inspect, verify, recommend, or warrant any donated goods.
          Donors are solely responsible for the condition and safety of items they donate.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">5. Organization Responsibilities</h2>
        <p>
          Organizations that receive donated gear are responsible for inspecting all
          items before distributing them to end recipients. Organizations should verify
          that items are safe, clean, and appropriate for their intended use. The
          platform makes no guarantees about the quality, safety, or fitness of any
          donated goods.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">6. No Warranties</h2>
        <p>
          The platform is provided "as is" and "as available" without warranties of any
          kind, whether express or implied. Without limitation, the platform makes no
          guarantees regarding:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>The quality, safety, or condition of any donated goods</li>
          <li>The reliability, identity, or good faith of any user</li>
          <li>The availability or uptime of the platform</li>
          <li>The accuracy or completeness of any listing or user-provided information</li>
          <li>Whether any donation will actually be fulfilled</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
        <p>
          To the fullest extent permitted by law, the platform and its operator shall not
          be liable for any direct, indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or
          punitive damages arising out of or related to your use of the platform. This
          includes, without limitation, damages arising from:
        </p>
        <ul class="list-disc list-inside mt-2 space-y-1">
          <li>Injury or harm caused by donated goods</li>
          <li>Interactions between users</li>
          <li>Loss of data or service interruptions</li>
          <li>Reliance on any information provided through the platform</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="mt-2">
          This is a free service. No money is exchanged. The platform's total liability
          to you for any claim arising from your use of the platform is $0.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">8. Indemnification</h2>
        <p>
          You agree to indemnify, defend, and hold harmless the platform and its
          operator from any claims, damages, losses, liabilities, and expenses
          (including reasonable attorneys' fees) arising out of or related to your use
          of the platform, your content, your donations, or your violation of these
          terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">9. User Content</h2>
        <p>
          You retain ownership of any content you post on the platform, including
          listings, descriptions, and images. By posting content, you grant the platform
          a non-exclusive, royalty-free, worldwide license to display, reproduce, and
          distribute that content solely for the purpose of operating the platform.
        </p>
        <p class="mt-2">
          You are solely responsible for the content you post. The platform may remove
          any content at its discretion without notice.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">10. Section 230 Notice</h2>
        <p>
          Under Section 230 of the Communications Decency Act (47 U.S.C. &sect; 230),
          the platform is not the publisher or speaker of user-generated content.
          Listings, messages, and other content posted by users represent the views of
          those users, not the platform. The platform does not endorse, verify, or take
          responsibility for any user-generated content.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">11. Privacy</h2>
        <p>
          Your use of the platform is also governed by our
          <a href="/privacy" class="text-[#2D4A2D] underline">Privacy Policy</a>,
          which describes how we collect, use, and protect your information.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">12. Modifications</h2>
        <p>
          These terms may be updated from time to time. Changes will be posted on this
          page with an updated date. Your continued use of the platform after changes
          are posted constitutes your acceptance of the revised terms.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">13. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          Questions about these terms? Reach out at
          <a href="mailto:terms@runnersinneed.org" class="text-[#2D4A2D] underline">terms@runnersinneed.org</a>.
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
